               <p>
            
               
                  <persName id="t16870512-26-defend111" type="defendantName">
                     Mary 
                     Wright
                  <interp inst="t16870512-26-defend111" type="surname" value="Wright"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870512-26-defend111" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870512-26-defend111" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , of the Parish of <placeName id="t16870512-26-defloc121">St. Sepulchres</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t16870512-26-defloc121" type="placeName" value="St. Sepulchres"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t16870512-26-defloc121" type="type" value="defendantHome"></interp>
                  <join result="persNamePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870512-26-defend111 t16870512-26-defloc121"></join>, was tryed for <rs id="t16870512-26-off122" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16870512-26-off122" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870512-26-off122" type="offenceSubcategory" value="other"></interp>
               stealing one pair of Sheets, a Pillowbear, Calico Curtains, two Shirts, two Neckcloaths, &amp;c.
            </rs> from 
               <persName id="t16870512-26-victim112" type="victimName">
                  George 
                  Rice
               <interp inst="t16870512-26-victim112" type="surname" value="Rice"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870512-26-victim112" type="given" value="George"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870512-26-victim112" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870512-26-off122 t16870512-26-victim112"></join>
                  </persName>
            , on the <rs id="t16870512-26-cd123" type="crimeDate">25th. of April</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870512-26-off122 t16870512-26-cd123"></join>, and it being proved she had confessed her unlawful taking them, neither in the Court, she being altogether capable of denying the Fact, the Jury brought her in <rs id="t16870512-26-verdict124" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16870512-26-verdict124" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870512-26-verdict124" type="verdictSubcategory" value="theftunder1s"></interp>
               Guilty, yet in consideration it was her first Fact, only to the value of 10 d.
            </rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t16870512-26-punish125" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16870512-26-punish125" type="punishmentCategory" value="corporal"></interp>
